response.overview: Hosts Joe Pickett and Nick Prueher take you back in time to the pre-internet 90s to resurrect the best "tape traded" videos passed from weirdo to weirdo on VHS. Highlights include "Pastor Gas," "Metallica Drummer," celebrity outtakes featuring a drunk Orson Welles and a foul-mouthed Richard Simmons, and the greatest news bloopers of the last 40 years. Recorded live at the Bell House in Brooklyn, New York.
response.title: Tape Trading Classics
